		<div id="listings">
			<p>After almost ten years of producing a new article on the first of each month, I&#8217;ve decided to change the format of this web site just a little. For a year or so now, I&#8217;ve wanted to demonstrate some of the same cooking techniques that I present in my classes, but I felt that I couldn&#8217;t illustrate these techniques sufficiently with just still images. So, I&#8217;ve started to produce a series of videos instead. I&#8217;ve just completed the first two&#8212;they are listed below. My goal is to produce a new video each month, but not necessarily by the first. Occasionally, I&#8217;ll continue to add a new article to the site. I hope you enjoy the new additions to the site.</p>
			<div id="left">
				<p class="subhead">~ Recent Articles ~</p>
				<p class="listing first"><a class="tips" rel="left" href="articles/2010/tools" title="Circumstances have caused me to add  two new tools  to those already in the <i>&agrave; la carte</i> tool shed. The first is a nitrite calculator for use when making sausages and <i>p&acirc;t&eacute;s.</i> The second provides a means of estimating the starting temperature of water for doing passive low-temperature cooking, what some are calling &#8220;beer-cooler cooking.&#8221; It performs the thermodynamic equilibrium calculation for you.">A New Tool in the Tool Shed, Part 2</a></p>
				<p class="listing"><a class="tips" rel="left" href="articles/2010/tools/" title="There&#8217;s a new tool in the <i>&agrave; la carte</i> tool shed. It&#8217;s a  nutrition calculator  designed to calculate the nutrients of an entire recipe. Other free calculators available on the web only list nutrients for a single ingredient at a time. This new calculator allows you to sum the nutrients of all the ingredients in a recipe and then produce a PDF version of the results. Additionally, if you want to include an ingredient that is not part of the <i>USDA National Nutrient Database for Standard Reference</i>&#8212;no problem&#8212;you can add nutrients for any ingredient you have data for.">New Tool in the Tool Shed</a></p>
				<p class="listing last"><a class="tips" rel="left" href="articles/2009/ipod/" title="I have a great collection of gadgets in my kitchen. My newest &#8220;gadget,&#8221; an  iPod Touch,  is my current favorite. I didn&#8217;t buy it to use in the kitchen, but because I am often working in there, it&#8217;s there with me.">My New Best Friend in the Kitchen</a></p>
			</div>
